caption: Very disappointed with the apathetic and poor customer service.  After ordering on their website I waited several hours for my order to never arrive without any updates. I eventually had to call and cancel after waiting 3 hours for nothing. Super disappointed. I won’t order again especially since they seemed like they could care less for the inconvenience.
Awesome place I love their Ramen so much ♥
Kimchi over salted ramen was ok. Beer was solid.
Good beers and tasty apps. Didn't have entrees but it's a unique place and worth your time to check out
Delicious!
In general this place is great, staff is great, curry is fantastic.  Only complaint is the chicken here. It's always got this strange tough wet texture, not uncooked but not pleasant.
I got the ramen with chicken, lime, and coconut milk. It just wasn't for me. The flavors were balanced but it was missing that wow factor of traditional ramen.
Had a great time with friends!
Rode our bikes here and they decided not to serve food any more when we arrived at 8:25pm. We were bummed. They sent us to Pearl Street. Terrible service, wish we could have tried the food.
This place is great. Food is solidly above average. Drinks are a stand out. Service can’t be beat. Ask for Hillary!
Joe is the best waiter ever! Food is great and the atmosphere is really cool.
Service was great and food was just as good. Very accommodating with kids!  Cant wait to come back!
Great ramen

Great place to bring family and friends. Great service, lovely decor, and the food is authentic to Japanese cuisine! I felt like I had transported to Japan! The ramen, sushi, and pork buns are the best I have ever had with loads of toppings and options to choose from. The server was great when we asked what menu items to choose, especially when it came to the beer! Unique and interesting selections, I will be sure to come back.
The service is really bad at this place.  The beers are average at best.  Skip this one unless you want average beer and terrible service.
Just work through the menu.
One of my new favorite hangout spots. Service is great, and the food is always awesome 👍

Service was inattentive and not very schooled on Japanese food. Takoyaki is frozen when served. Beers are great. Wish instead of fries actual okonomiyaki was on menu. Otafuku please. Love Japanese style curry. Wish this location had arare too.
I loved the atmosphere! It's set in the basement. The old soundlab! They had a really good beer selection and as always, the ramen was on point.
Best ramen in buffalo. Great service and cocktails. Beers aren't my style but well crafted nonetheless
AMAZING FOOD! Great quality, big selection, and good service.
Delicious!!!  Such a great hidden gem!!
The beer was great we did a flight.  We tried the appetizers too.  They all tasted great.  The staff was friendly and helpful.

The weirdest things happen when I stop by Sato, first I see and catch up with a high-school crush, then a date tells me something she has shared with no one... I don't know, maybe it's the great beer or the Sake, but it's worth stopping by on a whim if you're in the neighborhood.
Good place
Really great, interesting craft beer choices. Pear Saison is bomb.. Much larger inside than from outside appearance. Had a wonderful experience.  Will definitely be going back for more..
(Translated by Google) Ramen so good !!  (Original) ラーメン so good !!
Good service and food!  Nice beerv selection of  their own brews

Great fusion of Buffalo food and what you'd find in an izakaya in Japan. I love their takoyaki, takoyaki inspired french fries, yakitori, and their wonderful drinks. The place has a very modern feel and is great for casual hangouts or bringing a date.

If you like Japanese cuisine, alcohol and you're kind of a weeb, this is the spot for you. I love the location and aesthetic if this place. My only negative to it is sometimes the service is shotty. For example I ordered gyoza and server brought out breaded katsu, kind of disappointed but the katsu was banging still lmao

We went here for food,  we had two different kinds of Yakitori, spare ribs, tuna sashimi and vegetarian ramen. Not much flavor, a little disappointed. Atmosphere is awesome, great location in a basement, very nostalgic.
Great food and reasonable priced!

Unbelievable that I have worked in downtown buffalo for years and never eaten here. This place is hands down the best Japanese ramen I've ever had. Plus, the portions they serve are good for two meals!
Great service at the bar for dinner. Different ambiance.

I've been going to Babas for years and I have always received great customer service and food. When you first walk in everyone speaks to you (unless they are super busy, which is understandable) but for the most part everyone acknowledges you. I've tried several things but my favorite is the chicken and rice with onions, peppers, tomatoes and feta cheese.
My first time to the Brew Pub, I eat at their other location Sato Ramon quite often. As usual, great food and beer in a great setting. Staff was very helpful and polite. I will be back agian.

Definitely did not have the greatest experience. Service was so slow, I understand there was only 1 waiter that night, but it took almost an hour to get our food. Ordered an appetizer that came after we got our entree... with no apologies about that. To top it all off my friend and I got serious food poisoning. Won’t be returning. I’d spend your money elsewhere!
Amazing
Some of the better ramen in the city. The beer is a little pricey but that's ok. The steamed buns are where it is at.
I was very impressed with the quality and price of the food.  Everything I ordered was excellent and it wasn't too expensive.  I would be back!
Great food, atmosphere and service. We have been for lunch and dinner and have yet to be disappointed.
Food was very good.  Wasn't very busy and service was still slow.
Fantastic ramen. A must try!
Great flavors
Great food amazing atmosphere. Service a little slow but having one waiter can't complain. Will definitely come back.
The food is very good & the drink selection is great. Really cool old building, you have to try it.
Great drinks, warm modern ambiance, best ramen ever!

Pearl Street Grill was super busy prior to a recent rock concert at nearby Key Center. Sato Brewpub proved to be a very suitable alternative one block north on Pearl. The sake was excellent though pricey. Most customers drank craft beer. The ramen curry dish was nicely flavored and an ample portion. Hip 80s and 90s music played overhead. The server was friendly and helpful. This is an unusual place, unlike any Japanese restaurant I have visited outside Japan.
Amazing vegan ramen

My husband, I, and another couple went here for dinner and drinks last night.  We had been thoroughly looking to coming here. We had heard great things about this place and had tried the beer at different events... the beer and drinks were good. Unfortunately the food was disappointing.  My husband and I love: Teton, Kunis, and Wasabi. We are not big fans of Ramen; maybe that's why we were disappointed.  We did not love the food, if you enjoy fried food and Ramen I would highly recommend this place. However; if you're looking for a good sushi place with a big bar selection definitely go to Teton.

I usually go to the Sato in Allentown which is a lot more cramped. This location has a lot more space and a better atmosphere. I had the salmon poke and it was really filling and the perfect amount of lime. I will definitely go to this location over the one in Allentown!

I have been here so many times for lunch and I swear it gets better every single time! I always get ramen, and I work down the street so it's hard not to go whenever I want to! I really love the atmosphere and think it's so cool that it's on the lower level and you have to walk downstairs. I have not tried any of the beers yet but will have to sometime I'm not going back to work right after.
Very Good Food !! I had a Pizza & it was De- li- cious  it has a Brickoven  which 2 My taste  cook's   everything  in the most De-li-cious Way  !! Loved it !!

The food here is phenomenal and the beer is just as good. Great atmosphere and the bartender Randy, is one of the best bartenders I have ever encountered. For some reason this place has not been busy during our 2 visits. This place should have a line out the door
Fantastic, fresh food, great beer, and an awesome staff. Came in from Philly for the Eagles game. The best place we’ve been to in Buffalo.
Foood was good.....super slow turtle service at nite tho....one BARTENDER at a packed bar.😔
Clean, comfortable.
Awesome ramen and decent beer list. Would recommend for lunch, dinner or happy hour.
Well hidden 110 pearl.  It's in the basement.  Head down stairs.  Food and atmosphere is great!
Food was good but the wait was a little long. Don't expect a quick meal.
Great food, drinks and atmosphere
Unbelievable appetizers
Food is good. No music and bring sunglasses, lights can give you a fn sun tan. So final answer- no atmosphere.
Amazing beer. Great food and awesome service
Delicious!

We stumbled upon this place yesterday whilst out for a walk and decided to check it out. The place is really cool being in a basement and the interior design is spot on. Small windows lets you see into the small and humble brewery. The staff was super friendly and quickly served us. We didn't stay for that long, so only tried some of their beers, but didn't have the time to try the food. The beers we had tasted really good and being a Belgian inspired brewery with a Japanese twist was spot on.

The hidden gem of Buffalo! Downtown near the waterfront in a hidden location, easily to go unnoticed next to Pearl Street Bar and Grill, Sato Brewpub blends a comfortable atmosphere with extremely pleasant service along with reasonable prices for great tasting Japanese cuisine. All food is super fresh and tastes natural and healthy, none of it greasy or slopped together. Not only the best Japanese food I have have in a restaurant in Buffalo but one of the best dining experiences I habe ever had! It isn't just Japanese food like you can get 'to-go' from a grocery store. Rather, all the menu items feel carefully curated by a chef with experience in the industry. The unique underground location in downtown Buffalo, along with great tasting Japanese cuisine and friendly service, all add up to a "must visit" whether you are a visitor stopping in town for a few days or a local who thought they knew every good restaurant the city had to offer!
High marks for the ramen and selection of Japanese whiskey.  Make take a bit longer than you might think to pick up a take-out order.

Went there for lunch. Pretty pricy for what you get. It amazes me how the prices here are more expensive than what I can get in NYC and the quality/taste/flavor is average (at best...and that’s really stretching it). Ordered the Gyudon.  This was a bit more on the sweet side. I could not taste the umami flavor, which should be at the base of the palette. Felt like they sweetened the sauce to cover up the lack of depth.
Interesting Beers!
Poor service. Very, very limited (legitimately) gluten free options.  Overpriced. A far, far cry from the Elmwood location.
This beer is as always innovative and delicious.  Also: Okonomiyaki Fries or BUST.
Get service and very good food. Loved the beer. It was there own October Fest
Food and service was great
Good tasting ramen at reasonable prices, clean setting.
Amazing food (ramen and small plates were both filling and delicious) and incredible beer with different but interesting flavors and inspired takes on classic varieties! Definitely worth a visit.
This place is unbelievable. Prices a little high but worth it.
Food was good, eat before you come, took an hour to get ramen at a Monday lunch, and then another 15 minutes for the side.
Mmmm inventive food. Mmmm inventive beer. Yes.

The food was pretty good and the ambience has a retro vibe to it. Place looks and feels nice. However, service, at least for us, wasn't great. There was just one waitress serving the whole entire restaurant. For some reason the waitress gave other tables priority over us. This kept us waiting for pretty much everything all throughout our meal and we were just two people so it wasn't much food either. Guess she didn't like us!
Took 40 minutes for my steak bowl.

What an awesome place!! Unique and fresh. Their beers are excellent, someone for every taste buds. The food is fresh, well prepared, very affordable. Excellent service. May go back every night I'm in town. You have to try the spice bomb!!!
Been a longtime fan of Sato on tomorrow and was excited to try this. Really enjoyed the small plates, beer, and atmosphere. Highly recommended.

Too bad we didn't get to try any beer, which is all brewed in house, but the whiskey flight and cocktails were too tempting. Now we have another good reason to come back. Kimchi was just right and the ramen was A+. Staff were keen, friendly and helpful and we look forward to another visit.
Good vibe, nice selection of beer, friendly atmosphere. Going to return for dinner. Menu looks awesome!
Great food & service!
Okonomiyaki fries are a must try! Great beer, too!
Great food
Super chill place with great twist on beer. Food was also amazing.
Best ramen and really good craft brews
Beer. Noodles. Godzilla.

Good food and some pretty good and interesting beer flavors however it was not the best ramen I've had or the best beer. I should add it was also a very nice place and had good service so if your looking for some interesting craft beer and ramen this is a no brainier but if you are looking for the best ramen or best beer joint keep looking.
Go for ramen. Stay for their beer.
Enjoy the food.

Our server Meg was prompt but not pushy, really sweet with my friend's toddler. The beers are unique and excellent. I had a fun drink special with a shark-bitten lemon rind surfboard. Food was delicious!
Unexpected venue. Excellent food,as I am not a adventurous eater the meals I had were amazing. I highly recommend it.
Absolutely fantastic. I highly recommend the steamed bun, it is delightful.
Fun environment
Always great food and atmosphere! Best place for ramen in town!
Food and beer we're good but pricy

Really interesting fusion of Japanese food with on-site brewed beer. Even the beer had Japanese influences.  The pub food was very tasty, if a touch expensive for the serving size. Beer was amazing with several different style house brews on tap.  Atmosphere was more laid back than most pubs and decor was quite modern/minimalist/industrial. Worked well with the upscale menus and Japanese theme.  An excellent quiet evening with friends.

I can’t get enough of this place. I crave it at least once a week. I’m a creature of habit and always get ramen, but I have tried many other items and I’m never disappointed! Make sure you make a reservation, as this place is always packed. They have community tables you can sit at, but those are often full as well.
Unique place with a great vibe and awesome beers.

I had the Tori Miso Ramen and one of their house made draft beers. Each was good individually, but I don't recommend getting them together; their combined liquid volume is too much and the flavors clashed. The ramen was delicious; the broth was excellent with and without the extra spice bomb that I ordered.
Brewery meets Japanese restaurant. Lots of choices on the menu. Great sake too.
Great atmosphere. Octopus balls are tremendous.!

I work across the street from Sato. we order lunch or dinner there at least once a week. called today to order got put on "hold", which was the bartender setting the phone down.  waited for 10 minutes while he had a casual conversation with a friend. tried calling back and couldn't get through for 20 minutes because he never going the phone back up. called again and he did the same thing,  not giving me a chance to object.  Walked over to order in person and see what the issue was and the bar tenders were too busy doing shots at 2pm and chatting it up.  Extremely poor service.  Then they wouldn't let us order salmon even though we're had been trying to order for an hour. Will never order or go back.  They have lost a 10 person order twice a week.

Friggin Amazing!! A small plate of Pork Nachos. Fried wontons, ground pork and all the nacho accroutrmonts will make you want to order 10 of these, seriously. Then, a unique IPA, brewed with bonito flakes and produces a salty and umami beer that dances on the palate. So good, I resort to terribel, normal words. Enjoy, tho.
Great food and service! And awesome beer!

Love this place! Food is amazing, and the beer selection is fantastic! The cocktails are unique and interesting, and offer a nice enhancement to the menu. Don't be afraid of the Bonito beer, it's like nothing you'll have anywhere else!
I dashed here, and it looks really good and smelled really good. Very clean definitely would've eatin here 😄

I am so glad that the Sato chain keeps expanding. I have been wanting a ramen place locally for a long time. And to have all the extra Japanese cuisine to go along with it is a huge bonus.  The brewpub side deff makes up some interesting blends, Easter brews were especially interesting. Keep up the great work, and looking forward to my next visit.
Great location, love the Ramen
Very nice if you like good food and cocktails.
Great Beer OK food
Good food
Delicious! Friendly staff, they we're slammed and still maintained a positive attitude. Get a reservation if you want seats, however the bar is pretty nice as well.
Delicious!

I like the people here and atmosphere was nice. The food came really fast. I would save a five-star rating for place that was mind blowing. To me this food was good and affordable. And considering where it is, so near the key center, it might be the best option around.
The service and decor were great. I liked my pork bao bun, it had a good combination of flavors and the steamed break was nicely chewy. The veggie skewers were light on the seasoning.
Amazing food and service! The ramen bowls are to die for. ♥️🍜
I really thought this place was going to be good. It had to be the worst meal I've had in a while. Definitely won't be going back.
Great place! Super quick, reasonably priced and very tasty! You should go, it feels like a NYC restaurant with the split level entry, really cool. Excellent beer and cocktail offerings
Great food, unique quality beers, friendly staff, and a fun, cool vibe!!
The location is not the best
Delicious! highly recommend! Will return in warmer weather because the entrance is very drafty, Steep stairs and slippery when icy and wet.
Had octopus ball appetizer and bacon wrapped scallop skewers. Food was very good, and bartender Hillary was very friendly and helpful. Will definitely come back!
Great atmosphere..Great Beer & even Greater people...

Excellent spot for groups or a romantic dinner. I have eaten here multiple times, most recently for a date night with my wife. This is my favorite of all the Sato locations.  Their Japanese Inspired cocktails are also excellent as well as their selection of Japanese whiskey.
Love this place great beer selction
Small earthy meets Japanese decor, unique beer. Friendly server.. all in an obscure basement location.
Excellent Japanese style Belgian beers and amazing food. I'd recommend the ramen!

Out of this world Ramen - for Buffalo, but don't let that steer you away.  Having this as a local food option if you work in downtown is a real treat. The food is fantastic, especially the Okonomiyaki fries and their ramen selection. Their chicken karaage is fantastic as well, but get that when you're dining in, not taking out.  The murals on the wall give this hidden little food gem even more flare, but be aware, this is a pretty small place. If you are coming in around lunch time or at regular dinner times, the service can be quite slow. Every time we have gone into Sato, we've also noted they are out of menu items, which can be especially weird when it's at random times during the week.  I'm not sure they have an accessible entrance, which is a bummer if you have mobility impairments.
This Sato Brewpub is a very nice and clean. The service crew were friendly and nice.
The food is delicious every time.
Paitan Ramen is very oily. other than that, Yaki-tori, Kara-age are quite OK.
Fun night out on the town!

Nice atmosphere, very clean, food was tasty and fresh. Went mid-afternoon on a weekend with young kids. Bonus points for the kids menu! Ramen was very tasty. Next time plan to try the meat skewers. Server was exceptional - on top of everything without being overbearing. She was terrific with the kids too.
Great food and drink selection
Great food!!! Great drinks!!! Great service!!!
Steven is a great bartender. Their late night menu might look unassuming but there isn't a thing on it that I wouldn't recommend.
Food is tasty, place can get cramped but worth the visit

Fantastic place. Everything was perfect. We drove in for the hockey game and randomly chose Sato to spend the evening for my 40th birthday. Everything we had was delicious and top-notch, from the greeting, the service, the beers and the food as well as the cleanliness of the restrooms. I highly recommend this establishment to anybody who's never been as well as out-of-towners looking for high quality brewpubs. Thank you Sato Brewpub for an enjoyable evening!
Food is delicious. 😋 I have to order 1/2 the menu every time I go, because I just can't decide. Oh and pick any cocktail with yuzu, you won't be sorry.
My favorite restaurant in town. The food is great. And $5 mules is a fantastic deal
Great small plates and delicious Ramen!
Great food, great beer, great service.  We will be back!
Love the food. And yes. It is legit Japanese food and the vibes. This place brought back memories of my time spent in Japan.
Delicious ramen, interesting drafts. Try the salmon poke bowl

The ramen bowl was good but service not so much. I asked what the difference between the two broths were and she didn't have a clue. Service was slow and we could never find her. She was busy talking to co-workers at bar. I like craft beers but these ones weren't for me. Odd flavors made with squash & other items.
Best Ramen in the city.

This is a great place to eat and visit.  They have a great selection of house brewed beer and a Japanese infused menu.  My husband and I ordered the ramen and gyoza off of the late night menu.  Not only was the food and drinks great, but the atmosphere is as well.  We love the mural, which  displays different Japanese Beasts among a backdrop of downtown Buffalo scenes..very quirky!
Fun place, different menu than the other Sato's. We loved it!
Very delicious and fun place to smorgasbord with friends.
great spot
Good taste for my first ramen bowl.
HOLY SATO SAMURAI BATMAN THIS PLACE SLAPS YOU WITH RAMEN AND A COZY ENVIRONMENT AND YOU CRY BEGGING FOR MORE!
Fun place. Cool to try the Japanese interpretation of American beers. Great food to boot!
Fabulous work dinner, low cost and unbelievable food and drinks. This is going to be a hidden gem for buffalo, Sato always a top name for Japanese cuisine! Highly recommend!
Slow service but great food and beer.

Well I have not tried all the foods offered, so this also based off the company I was keeping.  I love its location and it has good selection of brewed beers. Plus options for none beer drinkers (which I think is perfect...my wife was happy). I definitely will go back!
I worked in the kitchen and let's just say if you saw behind the curtain you wouldn't be happy either
Great place for Japaneezy bites and Jabeer
Very down-to-Earth place with great food and drinks!
Good food, great beer and great whisky.

Food has never been dissapointing here. The drinks are cook and the ambiance is amazing. The one star has been taken away because of the unpredictable service. I've has nights with amazing service and others with not so amazing. Also, love the mural on the wall.
AMAZING
Great tucked away place!
Cool place with lots of vegan options!
Tasty food and drinks. A little piece of Japan in Buffalo.
Great craft beer that you can only get in house and delicious Japanese style cuisine. Try the wings and the ribs and their gourmet ramen is amazing!

I've never had ramen before my visit to Sato and I was not disappointed! I tried a variety of things since I went with some friends such as the steamed bun, a variety of kabobs, a rice bowl, spring rolls, wings, and fries with kewpie sauce. All with a flight of housemade beer. Highly recommend and will definitely be going back!
The beer and meat skewers here are amazing.
Fantastic beer and great food !
I am a few items away from tasting everything on their menu. And the best way, I get to start all over again.

Was really taken back by how delicious ALL of the beers were. I enjoyed a flight, and even though some of them may not have been my style of choice, the execution was excellent. Haven't had a meal yet, but everything I have eaten from the SATO family has been lights out.
Restaurant gave up our reservation for 14 the another group of peoe because we showed up 10 minutes early. Waiter then threw up his hands and said "well I can't turn back time!"
Excellent Japanese type cuisine with micro brews. One of the better places in Buffalo if you are not looking for more wings.
Love the food and staff.
Terrific ramen.on a chilly night!
Great food, good beer. Vegan options (but some are fried together with meat)
Very good food here. My wife and I had different ramen and liked both, and split some fried snapper. I think this was my favorite ramen to date.

We have been here before, great beer and good food. Stopped here tonight, the restaurant was about half full. We sat for 15 minutes waiting for service. There were only 2 servers and neither stopped at our table or told us someone would be with us shortly. They both walked by us several times and waited on tables on either side of us.  We were not in a hurry and would have been happy to wait if anyone even acknowledged we were there. I picked this spot for my birthday dinner and was very disappointed. After 15 minutes we left.
The food was great and came out very fast. But service was slow at the beginning and I have a hard time paying $7 for a 10 oz pour. If the beer was better priced it would be better.

Loved the relaxed atmoshere and ability to grab a table on a Friday night ! With sports on tv, I much enjoyed the very generous portion of green curry ramen I ordered. Interesting beer list. Can't wait to go back!
Great food and drinks but expensive
Really good Japanese food and some interesting beer.  Great place for lunch
Food is always delicious! They have my favorite ramen. They are also sensitive and accommodating to allergens/vegan requests, including market menu items. The atmosphere is fun, too.

Came here for dinner recently and order the Miso Ramen. I love the ramen at the other two Sato locations and was looking forward to having it again, but the ramen at the brewpub was just plain disappointing. The broth was watery and had no flavor. I don't know if they're skipping the pork bone broth or what, but it's very bland. It's also a smaller bowl of ramen compared to the other two locations, yet the price is the same.
The live band was fun. The lights need to be dimmed during music for atmosphere. Great underground establishment
Great food and beer. Had the sashimi, ramen, and potato salad and it was all amazing
Delicious food and an amazing cocktail menu!

Ramen and Craft beer brewed on site. What more can I ask for? The best pork bun I've ever eaten I guess because I got that too. This was one of the best meals I had in Buffalo and was one of the better meals I've had anywhere. Really liked the fact the chasu was chicken instead of pork. Loved the egg. Amazing broth. But the pork bun appetizer was the best part.
Loved this place
Fantastic ramen bowls, delicious complex flavour profiles on both the food and the beer. Worth  a visit and reasonably priced.

Excellent food and beer, and a great addition to the downtown food scene in Buffalo. I have to admit that their beer styles are not going to be to everyone's liking, especially people who are used to a lot of traditional adjunct lagers and pale ales. They are doing some inventive and even downright crazy things. However, if you keep an open mind you'll find lots of delights. The menu is very tasty and you can get a filling Japanese-inspired meal for a great value. I recommend picking a couple small plates to share if you have a lighter appetite and you'll be fine!
The non vegan food is excellent. Be weary ordering Vegan however. ordered a supposed vegan dish and it had cheese in it.
Amazing, inconspicuous place with great food and drinks. We highly recommend the bacon wrapped scallops.

Cool little downstairs spot. Unassuming front door on the street. Kinda reminds me of one of my fav NYC spots Hagi near Times Square. Pretty good diverse Japanese traditional menu with a mix of ramen, bowls, yakatori, sashimi at fair prices (I'm from LA so it was kinda inexpensive for me!)  Lots of good shareable apps so bringing friends is prob a good time. I'd love to see them have actual Japanese beer here...kinda a let down but not enough to cost them a star...because their house beers arent the same to me when you're in a Japanese place. You just have to have asahi...you know???
Love the Ramen here, and I have enjoyed the 3 beers that I tried. Great place for a quick lunch for anyone who works downtown as well.
I've only been in for lunch, but the food is great and the beer brewed on site ain't bad either
Undercooked pork belly that made my whole family sick. Ramen was subpar but definitely good for buffalo ramen.
Great service, interesting artisan drink options
First time there, and it's really tasty food. Went with friends and tried a little of everything that everyone had. Really impressed with it.

I've been here a couple times with work groups and it's great because we can get a bunch of dishes to share. Not many places like this in the downtown area! Everything has been great but the fast pickled cucumbers are something I will go back for.
Decent food and good selection of beer. Nice location close to the ballpark, KeyBank center, Canalside, etc... Nice artwork inside on the wall.
I come to Sato as often as possible! All three locations in buffalo have the best ramen I've ever had.
The food was great, and the drinks and service were excellent as well! Would def recommend it!

The atmosphere is great and so is the food. The brewpub is a perfect mix between Sato Ramen and the original Sato restaurant on Elmwood. It's more casual than Sato and has a more extensive menu than Sato Ramen. If you like either of the other Sato locations, definitely give the brewpub a try!
Little pricey, but always tastey
A bit pricey but excellent food. Planning on coming back and trying some beer/ adult beverages.
Nice clean place and great food
Absolutely Amazing wanted to try something different and I was very impressed with the food and the staff
The spice bomb for the ramen is amazing. Could use to give the table more water but I mean, who would take off a star for that?
Fun relaxed environment for cultural pub food!

Tasty food and micro brews made on site. The menu is really fun, as you are meant to order several snacks and small plates. My friends and I tried the tuna poke, cucumber salad, okonomiyaki fries, veg ramen, tan tan bowl, and curry pan. Everything came out as it was ready, letting you snack through each small item as you enjoy your beer.
1st time at Sato Brewpub. Had a great experience!  Beers were spot on and top quality! True to style. And the food was fantastic as well! Will be coming back soon!
Love coming here for sake and the food is great!!
Great bar with awesome craft beer.
Underground cool place.
The food was good and there was a nice atmosphere but the prices were a little high for the size of the portions. Good place to eat every once in a while!
Amazing place with great food and a fantastic drink selection

Nice modern space, very clean. You can try a “pre-selected” flight of 4 beers for $10. Bar service could have been better as the bartender never checked on us or asked if we needed anything (not a busy night either). He chatted with friends behind the bar instead and ate dinner. I hope that the owners/employers at least allow their employees to take breaks to eat so they don’t have to do it on the job.

An incredible spot, a must-visit for locals and guests. Tasty, clever and beautiful house-brewed beers. An inspired and delicious menu. Caring and engaged staff, and just great vibes all around. Go here!!!
Great atmosphere with interesting dishes

Stopped in for the first time - only had time for a beer. I didn't realize that they brewed their own here. I wasn't crazy about my first beer, which was a miso based brew.
